Package model

Class Ticket

java.lang.Object
model.ElementoCine
model.Ticket
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPrecio
public final class Ticket extends ElementoCine implements IPrecio
Cinema Ticket Class to make Ticket objects, this is part of the core of this project. When a Ticket is created, an instance of this class is produced in a new Ticket object, such instance has all the necessary information about everything needed to identify every aspect of the ticket and the client inside the Cinema. It has several interesting attributes: 
  - numeroTicket: The number of this Ticket. Type: int
  - precio: This Ticket's price. Type: double
  - fechaGeneracion: This Ticket's generation date. Type: LocalDate
  - cliente: This Ticket's owner, this is the client that owns this ticket. Type: Cliente
  - elementosCine: Collection meant to store objects that inherits from the super class ElementoCine,
which are related and attached to this ticket particularly, this is the movie, function and theater hall, ergo Pelicula, Funcion and Sala objects. Type: HashMap<String, ElementoCine>
Since:
1.0

    • generarPrecio

      public void generarPrecio()
      Sets this ticket price based on a certain criteria.

      This method must be invoked just when the ticket has been created, once the creation has ocurred, this method verifies several attributes to set the price, as follows:

      1. The price starts with a base of $2.00, it verifies the theater hall type, adding a certain amount in every case: 

                  VIP   : +4
            4D    : +3
            3D"   : +2
            Normal: +0.50
      2. It verifies if the movie is a release or not, adding a certain amount in every case: 
                  true : +2
            false: +0.50
      3. It verifies if this corresponds to a Vermouth function, if true and only if simultaneously the theater hall type is not VIP, a 50% discount is calculated on the final price, otherwise the price persists as it was at the previous step.
      Specified by:
      generarPrecio in interface IPrecio
